This paper is about machine learning-based applications in IoT devices, which suggests that it could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories. The most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper proposes a hybrid network that combines different learning techniques to optimize performance on highly constrained IoT devices. Other likely categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.SY (Systems and Control). These categories are relevant because the paper discusses compression techniques and model design space, which are important topics in these fields.
